National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice released a statement condemning the murder of human rights and civil society activist Salwa Bugaighis in Benghazi, Libya. Rice had met Bugaighis in 2011 and was impressed by her courage and dedication to a peaceful and democratic Libya. The United States joins the Libyan people in mourning Bugaighis's death and urges all Libyans to reject violent extremists and continue working towards their aspirations.